**Files:** darwin/argus.nix, darwin/rocinante.nix

~80% identical code. Create a parameterized base:

```nix
# darwin/default.nix
{ hostname, extraHomeModules ? [], extraSystemModules ? [] }:
mkSystem {
  system = "aarch64-darwin";
  users = [ "george" ];
  homeModules = [ ./modules/home/macbook-pro-16in.nix ] ++ extraHomeModules;
  systemModules = baseModules ++ extraSystemModules;
}
```

## Summary
Darwin-specific system services using launchd need NixOS equivalents using systemd.

## Current Darwin services (modules/darwin/base.nix)

### launchd.daemons.maxfiles
Increases file descriptor limits. NixOS equivalent:
```nix
boot.kernel.sysctl = {
  "fs.file-max" = 1048576;
};
# Or systemd-based approach
```

### launchd.daemons.maxproc
Increases process limits. NixOS equivalent via sysctl or limits.conf.

## Current Darwin user services (home/george/darwin.nix)

### launchd.agents.ssh-add
Loads SSH keys into keychain. NixOS equivalent:
```nix
services.ssh-agent.enable = true;
# Or systemd user service
```

### launchd.agents.gpg-agent
GPG agent service. NixOS equivalent:
```nix
services.gpg-agent = {
  enable = true;
  enableSshSupport = true;
};
```

## Acceptance criteria
- [ ] Create systemd equivalents in modules/nixos/base.nix
- [ ] Create user service equivalents in modules/home/linux.nix
- [ ] Test service functionality on NixOS

**Files:**
- modules/darwin/george/dock-apps.nix (24 lines)
- modules/darwin/george/town-dock-apps.nix (27 lines)

85% overlap. Merge into single parametrized module:

```nix
{ config, lib, ... }: {
  options.dock.extraApps = lib.mkOption { default = []; };
  config.system.defaults.dock.persistent-apps =
    baseApps ++ config.dock.extraApps;
}
```
